The paper discusses the application of knowledge graph and question answering in the E-commerce customer service field, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes extensions to the classic SPO structure and enhances traditional KBQA with reasoning ability, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the management of real knowledge, which involves database (DB) techniques, making cs.DB a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, making cs.LG a possible sub-category.
